 MBOMBELA – Below is a list of tips to know if you are in an accident. • Police and emergency services must be contacted in case you or someone else has been injured. • You cannot move any vehicles before police have arrived. • Police will need to take a statement from you. • You need to provide police with your identity number and produce your drivers licence and vehicle licence. You also need to get it from the other party. • If there are any witnesses at the scene, you need their name and telephone number and address. •If the accident happens out of town it must be reported to the nearest police station if possible.The police will then issue an accident number which you will use for insurance purposes. •Make sure you also have the name , rank and contact number of the police officer who takes your statement.